holarship on contemporary China and that describe increasing dislocation and individualism and a lack of moral centeredness. By using food as a lens, she shows a more complex picture, where connectedness and sense of place continue to play an important role, even in the context of rapid change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Jan 2023) 0aAgriculture - Economic aspects - China - History - 21st century. 0aAgriculturexEconomic aspectszChinaxHistoryy21st century. 0aFood consumptionzChina. 0aFood supplyzChina. 0aRural familieszChina. 0aUrbanizationzChina. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aacademic.  achina.  achinese country.  achinese history.  achinese.  acountry.  acountryside.  aeastern world.  aelderly.  aethnographic.  aethnography.  afamine.  afood scarcity.  afood shortage.  agrowing old.  ahistory of china.  ahunger.  aidentity.  aindividualism.  aindustrial.  aindustrialization.  amigration.  amorals.  aplace.  arelationship to food.  arelationship with food.  arural china.  arural.  ascholarly.  ascholarship.  aworld history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052029351940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520966741423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520966741/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY